body:
Cython.Utils.OrderedSet did not have a `__bool__` function and so
was always treated as "true". The mean that Cython always generated
buffer-handling utility code (`if all_buffer_types:` in FusedNode.py)
even when just handling scalar types.

comment_data.body: Should we have a test for the opposite case? I don't think it's particularly useful for any except that if the fused dispatch code gets refactored then this test becomes irrelevant and we'd quite like to know that

commit.message:
Don't call __Pyx_ImportNumPyArrayTypeIfAvailable for every fused def function

Cython.Utils.OrderedSet did not have a `__bool__` function and so
was always treated as "true". The mean that Cython always generated
buffer-handling utility code (`if all_buffer_types:` in FusedNode.py)
even when just handling scalar types.
Add Py2 __nonzero__ to generate the same C code from Py2
